1
00:01:35,430 --> 00:01:36,710
Come on, slow down, slow down.

2
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:40,430
Come, Jizi, sit.

3
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:41,230
No, no, no.

4
00:01:41,230 --> 00:01:42,230
Division Commander, you sit, you sit.

5
00:01:42,230 --> 00:01:43,150
Just sit down.

6
00:01:43,680 --> 00:01:44,120
You, you...

7
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:46,040
If I tell you to sit, just sit.

8
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,870
Here are paper and a pen.

9
00:01:53,350 --> 00:01:55,710
Just write down everything from

10
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,400
leaving the camp to returning.

11
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,230
Who you met,

12
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,920
what was said,

13
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:02,590
and what happened.

14
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:04,510
Including eating, drinking, shitting, and sleeping.

15
00:02:04,510 --> 00:02:05,430
How many times you used the latrine.

16
00:02:05,430 --> 00:02:07,000
Write it all down clearly for me.

17
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Plain and simple.

18
00:02:08,350 --> 00:02:10,560
If there's any lying or hiding...

19
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:13,120
Division Commander, I understand, I understand.

20
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:15,240
If I can't even pass this test,

21
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:16,360
you wouldn't believe

22
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,910
I could pass Division Commander Liao's test.

23
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:21,750
Good brother.

24
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,280
You've worked hard.

25
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:35,870
Young Mistress! Young Mistress!

26
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:38,310
We found the Eldest Young Master.

27
00:02:38,470 --> 00:02:39,310
Really?

28
00:02:40,750 --> 00:02:41,630
Master Wen.

29
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:44,190
How is Sha'er?

30
00:02:44,190 --> 00:02:45,910
Is he okay? Has he lost weight?

31
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:47,590
Did he get sick being out there alone?

32
00:02:47,590 --> 00:02:48,870
Did he suffer a lot?

33
00:02:49,590 --> 00:02:50,630
He is doing very well.

34
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:52,360
I saw him, and he's even gained weight.

35
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:53,800
Eldest Young Master is capable.

36
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,310
He opened a hotpot restaurant.

37
00:02:55,630 --> 00:02:57,150
Opening branches everywhere.

38
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,190
He's also quite lucky with the ladies.

39
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:01,190
He's almost settled down out there.

40
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:03,120
Yu Zhen.

41
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:05,360
I came specifically to tell you,

42
00:03:05,710 --> 00:03:07,960
I delivered the message you asked me to.

43
00:03:09,150 --> 00:03:09,960
Rest assured.

44
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,840
Young Master Fan misses you too.

45
00:03:12,030 --> 00:03:13,870
He said he will definitely come back.

46
00:03:14,750 --> 00:03:15,800
Then why

47
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:17,800
didn't he come back with you?

48
00:03:18,710 --> 00:03:20,030
When we parted ways,

49
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:21,520
something unexpected happened.

50
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:23,470
What his situation is now,

51
00:03:24,030 --> 00:03:25,240
we don't know either.

52
00:03:25,430 --> 00:03:26,080
That's right.

53
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:28,310
He asked me to escort Troupe Leader Wen back.

54
00:03:28,470 --> 00:03:29,840
The situation was urgent.

55
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,680
Heaven watches over the lucky ones.

56
00:03:32,030 --> 00:03:34,190
Once he handles it, he will return.

57
00:03:39,310 --> 00:03:40,190
You said

58
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:41,910
he opened a hotpot restaurant.

59
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:44,520
What is the name of that place?

60
00:03:44,750 --> 00:03:45,680
Dongshihui.

61
00:03:51,710 --> 00:03:53,400
Why aren't you in the kitchen frying the base?

62
00:03:53,910 --> 00:03:55,840
You just guard the door all day.

63
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,680
He's the one who injured Commander Qin.

64
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:01,800
But the medical bills fall on us two.

65
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:03,840
You still expect him to come back?

66
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:04,800
If he doesn't come back,

67
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,120
I will go find him.

68
00:04:08,430 --> 00:04:09,590
You damn girl.

69
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:13,030
You don't run our business properly,

70
00:04:13,710 --> 00:04:15,360
just thinking about running off.

71
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:17,360
Is it even our business anymore?

72
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,080
The money all goes into Commander Qin's pocket.

73
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:20,360
I'm done frying the base for him.

74
00:04:22,870 --> 00:04:23,750
Tell Gan Xia'er to go.

75
00:04:26,510 --> 00:04:30,360
Since you know Gan Xia'er is a spy from across the street,

76
00:04:30,510 --> 00:04:32,360
why do you still keep him?

77
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:35,000
Gan Xia'er is already an outcast over there.

78
00:04:35,190 --> 00:04:36,680
If I kick him out too,

79
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:38,750
his old mother won't have anywhere to get medicine.

80
00:04:39,870 --> 00:04:40,800
I believe

81
00:04:42,070 --> 00:04:43,720
this is also what Brother Fan would want.

82
00:04:45,390 --> 00:04:47,600
He knows to care for his old mother,

83
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:50,070
so you should think about your old man too.

84
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:52,680
It's precisely because you have the secret recipe

85
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:55,950
that Commander Qin hasn't dared to harm us.

86
00:04:57,430 --> 00:04:59,240
If our business collapses,

87
00:05:01,870 --> 00:05:02,950
in this town,

88
00:05:03,270 --> 00:05:05,070
we won't be able to stay.

89
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:22,830
Have a drink

90
00:05:25,070 --> 00:05:26,720
Don't listen to his nonsense

91
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,920
That Scarface is just a punk

92
00:05:31,270 --> 00:05:32,600
When you were being buried alive...

93
00:05:32,830 --> 00:05:34,310
It wasn't that I didn't want to save you

94
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,750
There were so many people there

95
00:05:36,190 --> 00:05:37,160
I couldn't do anything

96
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:38,430
Besides...

97
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,630
I really didn't steal your family's grain

98
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,920
Let's not talk about that

99
00:05:42,830 --> 00:05:44,160
How did you become a bandit?

100
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:45,270
It's all because of you

101
00:05:45,630 --> 00:05:46,950
Knowing you weren't dead...

102
00:05:47,190 --> 00:05:49,430
I led the brothers everywhere looking for you

103
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:50,510
While we were searching...

104
00:05:50,830 --> 00:05:52,560
We got abducted here and became bandits

105
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:53,560
So it's my fault?

106
00:05:55,390 --> 00:05:56,480
Then let me out

107
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:57,510
Let's escape together

108
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,270
If I could escape, I would have long ago

109
00:05:59,390 --> 00:06:00,510
I'm locked up here

110
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,160
We're going to die anyway

111
00:06:03,390 --> 00:06:04,630
I'm not gonna die

112
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,120
Someone's coming

113
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:28,920
Brother Fan

114
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,310
Brother Scar

115
00:06:31,270 --> 00:06:31,950
Brother Fan...

116
00:06:32,430 --> 00:06:34,480
Is there something you haven't confessed?

117
00:06:35,390 --> 00:06:36,310
Brother Fan

118
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:37,680
I'm asking if you...

119
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,070
...haven't confessed something

120
00:06:40,430 --> 00:06:41,070
I...

121
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,680
...have confessed everything

122
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:45,720
That's strange then

123
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,750
This place is short on manpower

124
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,600
Usually they don't kill newcomers

125
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,600
Just tell me the honest truth

126
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,160
So I can go plead for you

127
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:55,190
You're a real man too

128
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:58,240
Do you remember my favor?

129
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:58,830
I do

130
00:06:58,830 --> 00:06:59,750
Do you appreciate my help?

131
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:00,240
I do

132
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,360
Will you take me to escape?

133
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,920
Escape my ass

134
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,680
Tiger Ma is ruthless

135
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,190
The terrain here is complex

136
00:07:07,310 --> 00:07:08,830
There's no way in hell to escape

137
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,240
Stop talking nonsense

138
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:33,950
This is the last meal.

139
00:07:34,190 --> 00:07:35,510
I got you something good to eat.

140
00:07:39,870 --> 00:07:41,390
We're about to die anyway.

141
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:43,560
How can I eat anything?

142
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:45,720
You still have to eat.

143
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,360
Or you'll become a starving ghost.

144
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,240
The two of us...

145
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,560
let's eat together.

146
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,040
You don't even know me.

147
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:54,240
Yet you ask me to eat with you.

148
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:55,310
Anyway...

149
00:07:55,630 --> 00:07:56,800
you're not a bandit.

150
00:07:57,070 --> 00:07:58,510
Look at your face.

151
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:00,480
You have delicate features.

152
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,270
You must be a good person.

153
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,480
Probably just like me.

154
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:08,360
A fellow sufferer wandering the world.

155
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:11,360
Where are you from, and where are you going?

156
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:15,390
A fortune teller told me to head west.

157
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:18,630
I kept walking and ended up here.

158
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:20,950
You actually believe in fate?

159
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:22,190
I don't believe in fate.

160
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:23,560
But...

161
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,800
I have nowhere else to go.

162
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:31,600
A young girl like you...

163
00:08:32,310 --> 00:08:34,750
surviving in a place like this...

164
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:37,680
must have suffered a lot.

165
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:40,750
How did you get here?

166
00:08:41,550 --> 00:08:43,240
I was supposed to get married.

167
00:08:43,910 --> 00:08:45,120
But the elders in my family...

168
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,600
offended someone powerful.

169
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:50,030
To appease his anger...

170
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:52,000
they offered me to him.

171
00:08:52,910 --> 00:08:54,670
So he wouldn't kill everyone.

172
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:56,790
After he tortured me enough...

173
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,720
he negotiated with the bandits...

174
00:09:00,030 --> 00:09:02,630
and sent me here as a bargaining chip.

175
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,550
How pitiful.

176
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,750
How tragic.

177
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:09,840
If only you'd met me sooner.

178
00:09:10,390 --> 00:09:11,390
Otherwise...

179
00:09:11,910 --> 00:09:13,440
I would have taken revenge for you.

180
00:09:13,910 --> 00:09:15,270
We aren't related or anything.

181
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:16,960
You'd be willing to take revenge for me?

182
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:20,750
My ambition is to rob the rich to help the poor.

183
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:22,630
And enforce justice on behalf of Heaven.

184
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:23,720
Really?

185
00:09:23,910 --> 00:09:25,240
Right now...

186
00:09:25,790 --> 00:09:27,270
I can barely save myself.

187
00:09:27,390 --> 00:09:28,440
I can let you out.

188
00:09:29,030 --> 00:09:30,030
No, no, no.

189
00:09:30,550 --> 00:09:32,000
If you let me out...

190
00:09:32,390 --> 00:09:33,870
it'll get you in trouble.

191
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,390
As long as you're willing to avenge me.

192
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:41,720
Alright.

193
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:46,600
Then let's leave together.

194
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:47,440
Alright.

195
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,750
I'll go check if anyone's there.

196
00:09:48,870 --> 00:09:49,550
Okay.

197
00:09:55,790 --> 00:09:56,790
Quick, no one's there.

198
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:57,480
Let's go.

199
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,270
This way is blocked.

200
00:10:10,510 --> 00:10:11,440
Go that way.

201
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:15,320
We can't go there.

202
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:16,630
Then where?

203
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:17,840
Come on.

204
00:10:45,910 --> 00:10:47,320
There are two people there.

205
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:50,480
Let's climb down the wall over there.

206
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:50,840
Okay.

207
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:51,550
Let's go.

208
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:58,960
There's a rope here.

209
00:10:59,790 --> 00:11:00,550
Go this way.

210
00:11:00,550 --> 00:11:02,200
Going that way just takes you back, doesn't it?

211
00:11:08,910 --> 00:11:10,360
You're so strong.

212
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,390
It's so scary.

213
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:14,720
I'm scared to go down.

214
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:15,790
Then I'll go down first.

215
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,670
I'll catch you at the bottom.

216
00:11:17,750 --> 00:11:18,480
Alright.

217
00:11:30,390 --> 00:11:31,750
Come down, quick.

218
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:32,870
Okay.

219
00:11:34,390 --> 00:11:35,750
Be careful.

220
00:11:37,150 --> 00:11:38,200
I've got you.

221
00:11:46,870 --> 00:11:47,790
What was that?

222
00:11:48,870 --> 00:11:49,840
Who's there?

223
00:11:49,910 --> 00:11:50,960
What else could it be?

224
00:11:51,150 --> 00:11:52,080
Must be a wild boar.

225
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,150
Go patrol over there.

226
00:12:00,790 --> 00:12:01,390
Let's go.

227
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,630
I can't walk anymore.

228
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:05,390
I hurt my foot.

229
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:07,750
I'll carry you. Get up.

230
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:20,480
Division Commander.

231
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,670
I've finished writing.

232
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:35,480
It's very detailed.

233
00:12:37,670 --> 00:12:38,480
Good.

234
00:12:39,030 --> 00:12:40,000
Is it?

235
00:12:40,550 --> 00:12:41,510
Write it again.

236
00:12:45,510 --> 00:12:46,720
Write a better version.

237
00:12:58,390 --> 00:13:00,750
You won't get away carrying me like this.

238
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:03,390
Escape or not, we have to run.

239
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:04,840
But...

240
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:09,240
I really can't take it anymore right now.

241
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:10,080
Let's rest a bit first.

242
00:13:12,790 --> 00:13:13,390
I...

243
00:13:13,870 --> 00:13:15,320
I really can't walk anymore.

244
00:13:15,790 --> 00:13:17,200
Why don't you go on ahead?

245
00:13:17,510 --> 00:13:19,030
How is that possible?

246
00:13:19,670 --> 00:13:20,870
You saved me.

247
00:13:21,270 --> 00:13:22,910
How could I possibly leave you...

248
00:13:22,910 --> 00:13:23,790
...all alone here?

249
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:25,120
Besides...

250
00:13:25,390 --> 00:13:26,670
...a young girl...

251
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:28,910
...in a bandit's den...

252
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,510
...that just wouldn't be right.

253
00:13:31,790 --> 00:13:32,870
Let's try first.

254
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,480
See if you can walk.

255
00:13:38,870 --> 00:13:40,630
I'll help you, let's walk a bit.

256
00:13:40,870 --> 00:13:41,510
Let's go.

257
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:47,750
Is it any better?

258
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:48,870
It still hurts.

259
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:52,960
I'd better just carry you.

260
00:13:55,630 --> 00:13:57,440
Climb up yourself.

261
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:58,120
Okay.

262
00:14:00,870 --> 00:14:02,600
You call that climbing?

263
00:14:02,870 --> 00:14:04,600
You're pouncing on me!

264
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:06,120
How come...

265
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:07,750
...you're heavier than before?

266
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,080
Which way do we go?

267
00:14:10,510 --> 00:14:12,550
Go that way. Over there.

268
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:20,240
You pressed on my funny bone.

269
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:22,960
Laugh a little quieter.

270
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,670
Do you know how to massage?

271
00:14:28,790 --> 00:14:30,750
Us wandering practitioners...

272
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:33,030
...have to know a little bit of everything.

273
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:36,320
A young girl like you...

274
00:14:37,870 --> 00:14:39,030
...if I don't cure you...

275
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:41,960
...it'd be a shame if you ended up crippled.

276
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:46,870
Plus I have to take you on the run.

277
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,720
This bird's nest hair of yours...

278
00:15:08,910 --> 00:15:10,270
...looks too ugly.

279
00:15:10,510 --> 00:15:11,480
Come here, come here.

280
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:13,550
Let me comb it for you.

281
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:28,080
You know how to braid hair?

282
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:30,440
I used to braid my Missus's hair.

283
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:21,480
Young girls...

284
00:16:21,910 --> 00:16:24,200
...look good with two braids.

285
00:16:27,390 --> 00:16:28,030
Here.

286
00:16:34,150 --> 00:16:35,000
Here.

287
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,080
I'll eat this one.

288
00:16:37,510 --> 00:16:38,080
Okay.

289
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:39,630
Then I'll eat the mushrooms.

290
00:16:43,550 --> 00:16:44,360
So...

291
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:46,030
...where are we running to next?

292
00:16:47,790 --> 00:16:49,390
We'll go find the garrison.

293
00:16:49,630 --> 00:16:50,440
We can't go there.

294
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:55,000
What I mean is...

295
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:56,360
...whether we can escape or not...

296
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:57,440
...we don't even know yet.

297
00:16:58,510 --> 00:17:01,030
Only the army can fight bandits.

298
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,360
I've been thinking...

299
00:17:03,910 --> 00:17:05,080
...that fortune teller...

300
00:17:05,240 --> 00:17:06,960
...told me to keep going west.

301
00:17:07,080 --> 00:17:08,870
If I see someone with a gun, report to them.

302
00:17:09,390 --> 00:17:10,270
People with guns...

303
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:12,310
...if not bandits...

304
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:14,070
...must be the army.

305
00:17:15,550 --> 00:17:16,270
Not necessarily.

306
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:18,790
He told me to join the army.

307
00:17:19,030 --> 00:17:19,920
Join the army?

308
00:17:20,350 --> 00:17:22,000
Would they even recognize you?

309
00:17:22,550 --> 00:17:23,790
He gave me a...

310
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,920
...thing with a tiger head emblem drawn on it.

311
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:29,030
That might be a token of proof.

312
00:17:29,510 --> 00:17:30,200
Yeah.

313
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:32,880
This tiger head emblem...

314
00:17:33,590 --> 00:17:35,270
...I actually saw it...

315
00:17:35,510 --> 00:17:37,400
...on a soldier before.

316
00:17:37,590 --> 00:17:39,480
You saw it? Where?

317
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,000
It was on my sworn brother.

318
00:17:42,070 --> 00:17:43,110
What's his name?

319
00:17:43,110 --> 00:17:45,200
His surname is Wei, called Wei San'er.

320
00:17:47,550 --> 00:17:49,640
I saw it when we were bathing together.

321
00:17:50,830 --> 00:17:51,680
Brother.

322
00:17:54,070 --> 00:17:54,830
Big Brother.

323
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:00,110
On the back of his hand...

324
00:18:00,110 --> 00:18:01,880
...there was a tiger head emblem pattern.

325
00:18:02,550 --> 00:18:03,480
But...

326
00:18:04,830 --> 00:18:05,880
I can't...

327
00:18:07,830 --> 00:18:09,200
I'm not sure...

328
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:11,400
...if it's the same one.

329
00:18:18,550 --> 00:18:20,590
Wei San'er...

330
00:18:21,030 --> 00:18:24,790
...how could a fortune teller know him?

331
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,110
So...

332
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,790
...are you still going to help me get revenge?

333
00:18:38,750 --> 00:18:40,160
I will.

334
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:57,510
Mushrooms on the mountain...

335
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,350
...how can you just eat them randomly?

336
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:39,270
How did I end up back here?

337
00:19:41,440 --> 00:19:42,440
Where is that little girl?

338
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,070
Where is that little girl?

339
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:46,790
That little girl...

340
00:19:47,680 --> 00:19:49,960
I was the one who tricked her into going out.

341
00:19:50,750 --> 00:19:51,640
Don't blame her.

342
00:19:54,750 --> 00:19:55,720
Big Brother.

343
00:19:56,550 --> 00:19:57,750
Do me a favor.

344
00:19:57,750 --> 00:19:59,400
Let that little girl go.

345
00:20:35,790 --> 00:20:37,400
Boss Ma.

346
00:20:49,510 --> 00:20:50,830
Do I look good?

347
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:52,680
Boss Ma.

348
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,350
You are Tiger Ma?

349
00:20:54,350 --> 00:20:55,310
Who else?

350
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:57,640
I think...

351
00:20:58,350 --> 00:20:59,270
little girl,

352
00:20:59,750 --> 00:21:01,590
you'd look better with two braids.

353
00:21:01,880 --> 00:21:04,240
You look like a bad guy like this.

354
00:21:05,070 --> 00:21:06,200
Then do you think...

355
00:21:06,830 --> 00:21:08,000
I'm a good person?

356
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,590
Anyway, you're not a bad guy.

357
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:13,640
Let him go.

358
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:14,440
Yes.

359
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:16,160
Come here.

360
00:21:16,790 --> 00:21:18,070
Shut your mouth.

361
00:21:20,480 --> 00:21:21,400
Boss Ma.

362
00:21:21,550 --> 00:21:23,590
He is a little brother of mine.

363
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:25,270
When I roamed the world...

364
00:21:25,270 --> 00:21:26,440
he was always following me.

365
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:28,070
He has no bad intentions.

366
00:21:28,350 --> 00:21:29,070
Look...

367
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:31,270
can we add him to my squad?

368
00:21:31,830 --> 00:21:33,750
I'll definitely take him and teach him the rules properly.

369
00:21:33,880 --> 00:21:35,240
Why should he follow you?

370
00:21:36,110 --> 00:21:38,270
Logically speaking, he and I are old acquaintances too.

371
00:21:38,510 --> 00:21:39,880
Based on the headcount...

372
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,590
he should be assigned to my squad.

373
00:21:41,590 --> 00:21:42,350
You're everywhere, aren't you?

374
00:21:42,350 --> 00:21:43,030
What about it?

375
00:21:43,030 --> 00:21:44,160
He should be killed.

376
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:47,550
Why is it as soon as you speak,

377
00:21:47,550 --> 00:21:49,110
it's all about killing this and that?

378
00:21:49,750 --> 00:21:50,720
Who are you?

379
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:52,640
Who do you think you are?

380
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:55,880
Boss Ma hasn't even spoken yet.

381
00:21:56,350 --> 00:21:58,310
And here you are jabbering away.

382
00:21:58,310 --> 00:21:59,240
Let me ask you.

383
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:01,070
You guys...

384
00:22:01,590 --> 00:22:02,590
Boss Ma...

385
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:05,110
when she twisted her ankle...

386
00:22:05,750 --> 00:22:06,920
where were you all?

387
00:22:08,240 --> 00:22:10,030
When Boss Ma was hungry...

388
00:22:10,030 --> 00:22:10,960
where were you all?

389
00:22:11,070 --> 00:22:12,350
Boss Ma and I...

390
00:22:12,510 --> 00:22:14,480
have shared hardships together.

391
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:23,440
Actually,

392
00:22:23,830 --> 00:22:25,880
my coming up here was a misunderstanding.

393
00:22:26,110 --> 00:22:28,680
But with so many brothers here...

394
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:30,830
It's fate, after all

395
00:22:31,110 --> 00:22:32,720
If you were to kill me

396
00:22:34,110 --> 00:22:35,590
it would ruin your feng shui

397
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:39,030
So what about his men?

398
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:40,790
So what if I am his man?

399
00:22:40,920 --> 00:22:42,240
Actually, we are all

400
00:22:42,350 --> 00:22:43,830
Boss Ma's men

401
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:46,000
Well said

402
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:47,720
Since you want to be one of my men

403
00:22:48,030 --> 00:22:49,310
I'll grant your wish

404
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:51,310
Then I appoint you as

405
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:52,640
Strategist

406
00:22:53,350 --> 00:22:54,510
From now on

407
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:56,310
you answer only to me

408
00:22:58,310 --> 00:22:59,350
Strategist

409
00:22:59,790 --> 00:23:00,920
That won't do

410
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:03,200
Isn't he going to boss us around?

411
00:23:03,350 --> 00:23:04,680
This won't work

412
00:23:04,790 --> 00:23:06,110
That won't work either

413
00:23:06,310 --> 00:23:07,680
You're really hard to please

414
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:08,960
He already said

415
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:10,510
it's fate, isn't it?

416
00:23:11,350 --> 00:23:12,240
Will you take the job?

417
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:16,830
How am I worthy of this?

418
00:23:17,920 --> 00:23:19,720
Becoming an officer right upon arrival

419
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:21,590
As expected of Brother Fan

420
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:23,440
Brother Fan really is impressive

421
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:24,400
Congratulations, congratulations

422
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:25,350
Same to you, same to you

423
00:23:25,350 --> 00:23:26,070
Brother Fan

424
00:23:26,070 --> 00:23:28,270
I'll be relying on you from now on

425
00:23:28,350 --> 00:23:29,480
We'll look out for each other

426
00:23:29,830 --> 00:23:30,750
Brother Fan

427
00:23:31,750 --> 00:23:32,830
You really are formidable

428
00:23:33,030 --> 00:23:34,750
What's all the noise? Shut up

429
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:41,350
If my brother becomes an officer, I fully support it

430
00:23:41,750 --> 00:23:43,110
But to convince everyone

431
00:23:43,590 --> 00:23:44,920
you might need to submit a Proof of loyalty

432
00:23:44,920 --> 00:23:46,550
What kind of mess are you stirring up now?

433
00:23:46,550 --> 00:23:47,720
None of your damn business

434
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:49,550
I know my brother

435
00:23:50,030 --> 00:23:51,270
Since he is the Strategist

436
00:23:51,270 --> 00:23:52,750
he should lead everyone on a job

437
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:54,400
So you can all get a good look at

438
00:23:54,640 --> 00:23:56,720
my brother's resourcefulness

439
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:57,920
Big Brother

440
00:23:59,030 --> 00:24:00,880
You used to be the leader

441
00:24:01,480 --> 00:24:03,400
and we just followed behind your butt

442
00:24:03,550 --> 00:24:04,200
No, no, no

443
00:24:04,310 --> 00:24:06,240
Your past glory is not worth mentioning.

444
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:09,030
Now that Boss Ma thinks highly of you,

445
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:10,440
you must live up to

446
00:24:10,440 --> 00:24:12,750
Boss Ma's trust in you.

447
00:24:13,920 --> 00:24:15,030
This proposal works.

448
00:24:15,830 --> 00:24:17,240
If it fails,

449
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:19,110
you'll get a spanking.

450
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:21,240
Understood.

451
00:24:22,640 --> 00:24:23,270
Yes.

452
00:24:23,790 --> 00:24:24,960
So you're willing to believe me now?

453
00:24:26,480 --> 00:24:28,270
Your three reports are basically consistent.

454
00:24:28,510 --> 00:24:30,550
Which means it really happened.

455
00:24:30,830 --> 00:24:31,750
Drink water. Drink up.

456
00:24:36,350 --> 00:24:38,920
That Lucky General mentioned in your reports...

457
00:24:39,270 --> 00:24:40,480
Is he really that formidable?

458
00:24:41,510 --> 00:24:42,880
That man is really capable.

459
00:24:43,160 --> 00:24:45,000
No matter how dangerous the situation,

460
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:46,240
he can resolve it.

461
00:24:46,510 --> 00:24:48,240
The key is that he is righteous,

462
00:24:48,240 --> 00:24:49,160
and decisive in action.

463
00:24:49,200 --> 00:24:50,550
He's general material.

464
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:52,350
However,

465
00:24:53,110 --> 00:24:55,310
I'm not sure if he's willing to join the army.

466
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:56,680
I was afraid if I mentioned it right away,

467
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:58,590
and scared him off, it would be trouble.

468
00:24:59,030 --> 00:25:01,200
So I only gave him a token,

469
00:25:01,510 --> 00:25:02,680
and pointed him in a direction.

470
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:04,790
Thinking I'd trick him into coming here first,

471
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:07,110
then slowly convince him to serve you.

472
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:10,720
If he's really as formidable as you say,

473
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:13,830
and gets poached by other forces,

474
00:25:14,240 --> 00:25:15,550
that would be a bit troublesome.

475
00:25:16,030 --> 00:25:16,640
Division Commander,

476
00:25:17,030 --> 00:25:17,960
rest assured on this.

477
00:25:18,510 --> 00:25:19,680
With my friendship with him,

478
00:25:20,070 --> 00:25:20,790
it's a sure thing.

479
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:22,110
You're that sure?

480
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:23,400
If you are anxious,

481
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:24,830
I'll go out right now and bring him back.

482
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:26,440
What if you run off too?

483
00:25:27,270 --> 00:25:28,750
How could I possibly run?

484
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:29,480
Division Commander,

485
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:31,110
you just said you trusted me.

486
00:25:35,310 --> 00:25:37,590
You said you pointed him in a direction.

487
00:25:37,720 --> 00:25:38,310
Yes.

488
00:25:38,310 --> 00:25:40,000
And gave him a token.

489
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:40,750
Yes.

490
00:25:42,110 --> 00:25:44,640
But the man just hasn't arrived.

491
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:49,240
And I don't feel safe letting you go out again.

492
00:25:50,790 --> 00:25:52,920
I don't want you risking yourself.

493
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:57,160
The only plan for now

494
00:25:58,070 --> 00:25:59,480
is to wait.

495
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:00,680
That works too.

496
00:26:02,750 --> 00:26:03,880
I have a good idea.

497
00:26:04,110 --> 00:26:05,000
Division Commander, please speak.

498
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,510
If he doesn't arrive in three more days,

499
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:09,400
you skip one meal.

500
00:26:10,160 --> 00:26:11,510
If he doesn't arrive in six days,

501
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:13,400
you skip two meals.

502
00:26:13,720 --> 00:26:15,160
Until he shows up.

503
00:26:15,270 --> 00:26:16,790
When that time comes, I'll throw you a huge banquet,

504
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:17,880
and you can eat to your heart's content.

505
00:26:18,440 --> 00:26:19,640
If he doesn't come for a month...

506
00:26:19,790 --> 00:26:20,550
Don't say a month,

507
00:26:20,550 --> 00:26:22,400
I'd starve to death in half a month.

508
00:26:22,550 --> 00:26:23,480
How is that possible?

509
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:25,350
You and I are brothers, brothers for life.

510
00:26:25,350 --> 00:26:26,680
I'd whip up some rice soup,

511
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:28,200
just to keep you alive.

512
00:26:29,310 --> 00:26:30,480
Doesn't this count as torture?

513
00:26:32,750 --> 00:26:34,510
You're coughing, go see a doctor.

514
00:26:34,510 --> 00:26:35,480
Exactly.

515
00:26:36,640 --> 00:26:39,310
This is the merchant caravan.

516
00:26:40,110 --> 00:26:42,480
This is us.

517
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:46,160
This is you guys.

518
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:47,590
Who is this?

519
00:26:48,510 --> 00:26:49,270
This...

520
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,480
This is a tree branch.

521
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:54,070
Then where am I?

522
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:55,240
You want to go?

523
00:26:55,510 --> 00:26:57,830
It's his first time commanding, he has no experience.

524
00:26:57,830 --> 00:26:58,920
It's still very dangerous.

525
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:00,350
That's why I must go even more.

526
00:27:00,550 --> 00:27:01,680
If he runs into trouble,

527
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:03,160
I can remedy it in time.

528
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:04,400
I'm here, aren't I?

529
00:27:04,830 --> 00:27:06,400
You wait at home for the good news.

530
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:09,200
If we really encounter danger,

531
00:27:09,590 --> 00:27:10,920
won't you just protect me?

532
00:27:13,510 --> 00:27:14,960
I'll protect you with my life.

533
00:27:15,920 --> 00:27:16,510
Good.

534
00:27:17,510 --> 00:27:18,200
Brother Fan.

535
00:27:18,590 --> 00:27:20,310
Merchant caravans are very alert nowadays.

536
00:27:21,110 --> 00:27:22,350
At the slightest disturbance,

537
00:27:22,350 --> 00:27:23,310
they run away immediately.

538
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:24,480
Do you have any way

539
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:25,960
to catch these people off guard?

540
00:27:27,550 --> 00:27:30,480
I'll have my own way when the time comes.

541
00:27:47,270 --> 00:27:48,680
Here they come! Here they come!

542
00:27:50,350 --> 00:27:51,000
Hurry up!

543
00:27:54,680 --> 00:27:56,680
Enemies are bound to meet.

544
00:28:02,550 --> 00:28:04,550
Keep those three.

545
00:28:10,590 --> 00:28:11,590
Get ready.

546
00:28:18,270 --> 00:28:18,880
Cut them down!

547
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:18,070
Don't kill me! Don't kill me!

548
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:20,000
Go, go!

549
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:36,400
Don't move!

550
00:29:36,750 --> 00:29:37,400
Squat down!

551
00:29:37,720 --> 00:29:39,160
Check for survivors first.

552
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:48,110
Are you asleep?

553
00:29:48,750 --> 00:29:49,440
No.

554
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:50,510
Then are you hurt?

555
00:29:51,400 --> 00:29:52,640
No.

556
00:29:54,510 --> 00:29:55,750
Then what's wrong with you?

557
00:29:57,270 --> 00:29:58,440
I faint at the sight of blood.

558
00:29:58,790 --> 00:29:59,720
Thanks to you,

559
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,240
the brothers can have a few good meals again.

560
00:30:06,750 --> 00:30:07,400
Pack up.

561
00:30:07,590 --> 00:30:09,400
Let's go, let's go!

562
00:30:14,310 --> 00:30:15,440
Keep up in the back!

563
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:17,550
Let's go, Brother Fan.

564
00:30:19,110 --> 00:30:20,550
You'll get used to it.

565
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:23,110
Those three men...

566
00:30:23,240 --> 00:30:24,480
what are we taking them back for?

567
00:30:25,440 --> 00:30:27,200
To sleep with Tiger Ma.

568
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:28,750
Nonsense.

569
00:30:28,750 --> 00:30:30,480
What do you mean nonsense? I'm not talking nonsense!

570
00:30:30,750 --> 00:30:31,790
I saw it with my own eyes.

571
00:30:31,960 --> 00:30:33,790
Big Brother went into Tiger Ma's bedroom.

572
00:30:33,960 --> 00:30:35,480
After he came out, he was

573
00:30:35,920 --> 00:30:37,030
head over heels for Tiger Ma.

574
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:38,480
I heard Tiger Ma is organizing

575
00:30:38,480 --> 00:30:39,510
her own Suicide Squad.

576
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:41,350
Big Brother was the one selected.

577
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:43,680
But what they did inside the bedroom,

578
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:45,510
